        public static void insertIntoObservatory​(java.lang.String obsName,
                                         double areaCovered,
                                         int yearStarted,
                                         java.lang.String countryLocation)
        This method inserts the details of a new observatory into a relation in the database The details of this new observatory are gotten from the user through the javaFx program
        Parameters:
        obsName - This is the name of the observatory users would store their galamsey records in. It is of type String
        areaCovered - This is the area the galamsey report covers. It is of type int
        yearStarted - This is the year an observatory was started. It is of type int
        countryLocation - This is the country an observatory is located. It is of type String

        galamseyColVal - This is the Galamsey colour value
        yearOfEvent - This is the year the galamsey report started
        Longitude - This is the longitude of the location the galamsey report is based on
        Latitude - This is the latitude of the location the galamsey report is based on
        obs - This is the name of the observatory the galamsey report will be stored in

        public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Galamsey> loadGalObs​(java.lang.String obsName)
